text: George William Arnold from the National Institute of Standards & Technology, Gaithersburg, Maryland was named Fellow of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE) in 2012 for leadership in architecture and protocols for the electric grid and telecommunications network. ==References== Category:20th-century births Category:Living people Category:Fellow Members of the IEEE Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
